---
title: Cover Letter to Tenant
category: guidance
description: Non-statutory cover letter to send with Form 3
filename: cover_letter_to_tenant.pdf
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Cover Letter to Tenant</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: #222;
      max-width: 760px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .letterhead {
      margin-bottom: 2em;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
      padding-bottom: 1em;
    }

    .sender,
    .recipient {
      white-space: pre-line;
    }

    .meta {
      margin: 1em 0 1.5em 0;
    }

    .subject {
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 1.5em 0 0.75em 0;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .notice-box {
      border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
      background: #f6f6f6;
      padding: 1em;
      margin: 1em 0 1.5em 0;
    }

    .notice-box p {
      margin: 0.35em 0;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0.75em 0 0.75em 1.2em;
    }

    .closing {
      margin-top: 2em;
    }

    .small-note {
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #555;
      margin-top: 1.75em;
      border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
      padding-top: 0.75em;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="letterhead">
    <div class="sender">{{landlord_name}}</div>
    {{#if landlord_address}}<div class="sender">{{landlord_address}}</div>{{/if}}
  </div>

  <div class="recipient">
    {{tenant_name}}
    {{#if property_address}}
    {{property_address}}
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <div class="meta">
    <p><strong>Date:</strong> {{current_date}}</p>
    <p><strong>Property:</strong> {{property_address}}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="subject">Enclosed: {{notice_type}}</div>

  <p>Dear {{tenant_name}},</p>

  <p>Please find enclosed a {{notice_type}} relating to the above property.</p>

  <div class="notice-box">
    <p><strong>This letter is not the notice itself.</strong> The legal notice is the enclosed Form 3 notice.</p>
    {{#if service_date_formatted}}<p><strong>Date served:</strong> {{service_date_formatted}}</p>{{/if}}
    {{#if expiry_date}}<p><strong>Earliest date court action may be started:</strong> {{expiry_date}}</p>{{/if}}
    {{#if ground_descriptions}}<p><strong>Grounds relied on:</strong> {{ground_descriptions}}</p>{{/if}}
  </div>

  <p>Please read the enclosed notice carefully. It explains the possession grounds being relied on and the earliest date on which court proceedings may be started if the matter is not resolved first.</p>

  {{#if uses_rent_arrears_grounds}}
  <p>If this notice includes rent arrears grounds, you should contact the landlord or agent promptly if you wish to discuss payment, make a proposal, or explain any issue affecting the rent account.</p>
  {{/if}}

  <p>You may wish to seek independent advice as soon as possible. Sources of help can include Shelter, Citizens Advice, a housing adviser, your local authority housing team, or a solicitor.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Keep a copy of the enclosed notice and this letter.</li>
    <li>Take advice promptly if you disagree with the notice or need housing assistance.</li>
    <li>If you want to discuss the matter directly, use the contact details on the notice or any existing agreed contact route.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="closing">
    <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
    <p>{{landlord_name}}</p>
  </div>

  <p class="small-note">This covering letter is a support document provided for clarity. It is not itself a legal notice and does not replace the enclosed Form 3 notice.</p>
</body>
</html>
